Package me.recsfor.app

This package provides functionality for processing user data.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CredentialEncryption
    This class is used to encrypt user credentials (their password), so they can be securely stored in a database.
    ListData
    Converts user like and dislike data from JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) to a Java object.
    ListModel
    Defines the content of user like and dislike lists.
    UserBean
    JavaBeans component to store user data.

Package me.recsfor.app Description

This package provides functionality for processing user data. Upon submission of a user form, passwords are encrypted and validated. Once a user has been authenticated, their session data will be stored in a UserBean. User like and dislike lists are processed as JSON data. Data is synced with the frontend using localStorage.
